text: Orkdal is a former city in Trøndelag county, Norway. The city was founded in 1838. It was dissolved in 2020 when it joined Orkland Municipality. It had a population of 11,933 in 2020 and was the 188th largest city in Norway. ==References== Category:Cities in Norway Category:Former municipalities of Norway Category:Trøndelag
title: Orkdal
